 the\nplaygrounds, 'reported on the success\nat the- several i playgrounds .of the\nfourth, of July \"\\u25a0 celebrations and that\nthe cost-f.to the commission, was $1,457.\nHe added that since the fourth the at\ntendance at the North beach grounds\nhad increased 25,' per cent. He sug\ngested that a. woman be placed in\ncharge of -the girl's \"section. The ap\npointment wllirbe made.\n.Commissioner McLaren was request\ned to see that 750 trees,, shrubs and\nplants' are-' set '..ln' the Harrison street\ngrounds, which willbe ready for open\ning about September 1.,\nA plan for; the arrangement of the\ngirls' section 'of the. grounds at North\nbeach was presented by Director Schlit\nter and he was ordered to carry it out.\nIt was decided -to develop the Spring\nValley school^ site into a playground\nas. soon- as th,e shack. school is removed.\nA .-.finance- committee will bej ap\npointed to; apportion the $50,000\u00ab which\nhas .been allowed to the commission.\nWOMAN CONyiCTED OF\nI FLOURISHING REVOLVER\nMrs. Patricia Howard Fined $5\nf or G un Play\nMost of, -the: women roomers in the\napartment house ofMrs. E. R. Bertelot,\n931. Webster street, .were in Police\nJudge Deasy's court yesterday when\nthe case of Mrs. Patricia Howard,\ncharged with exhibiting a deadly wea\npon, was called for trial, .v\nMrs. Carrie Munroe. who was forced\nat the point of a revolver to go down on\nher knees and retrkct; the offensive\nnames she had called Mrs. Howard, tes\ntified, and she was '\\u25a0\\u25a0' followed- -by Mrs.\nPearl \u2022\"Williams; who took* the revolver\nfrom Mrs. Howard. ,\\u25a0 The landlady also\ntestified.; \\u25a0'\u2022\nMrs. Howard did not deny-thc charge,\nand the judge fined her $5.\nFRIDAY, .JIJLr 15: 1910.\nRATIONAL LIVING EXPOUNDEDi-Dr. hndolph\n11. Gerber, advocate- of rational lirlnz. U tn\ndeliver an address In the .'Auditorium,; Tage and\n\\u25a0Tilliriore Street*\", under the auspices of the San\nFrancisco i .materialist^- association Friday\neven